INSERT INTO "public"."pains_initial" ("id", "project_id", "segment_id", "pain_index", "name", "description", "deep_triggers", "examples", "approved_at") VALUES ('015298cd-0521-429f-ad41-89b6b7bb306d', '17d26309-520b-45ec-b5d5-92512e2f6620', 'f81beda1-abd9-4969-993c-05a62b4ff695', '4', 'Body betrayal and control loss grief', 'Profound grief and rage about their body no longer responding predictably to health interventions that worked in the past. Feeling betrayed by digestive issues, energy crashes, and declining resilience despite ''doing everything right.'' The loss of bodily control threatens their identity as someone who can manage their health through discipline and good choices.', '["Grieving the loss of their younger, more responsive body","Anger at feeling powerless against natural aging processes","Identity crisis when health discipline doesn''t guarantee results","Fear that their body is becoming unpredictable and uncontrollable","Shame about needing more help to maintain what used to be effortless"]', '["''I eat better and exercise more than people half my age but I feel worse - it''s not fair''","''My body used to bounce back from anything, now everything hurts and nothing works''","''I feel like I''m fighting a losing battle against my own biology''"]', '2025-12-01 13:17:49.094091+00'), ('04029971-1111-47e4-8fe7-fed2cf74bbd3', '17d26309-520b-45ec-b5d5-92512e2f6620', '260ec846-ba0f-43d5-82d9-4b2f93a4a440', '6', 'Expert Disappointment Pattern Trauma', 'Psychological trauma from repeatedly investing in premium, scientifically-marketed health solutions that fail despite their expert evaluation and perfect compliance. Each failure reinforces learned helplessness and makes them simultaneously more desperate and more skeptical, creating decision paralysis.', '["Learned helplessness from repeated supplement failures despite expert selection","Self-doubt about their ability to evaluate health products despite medical training","Pattern recognition that even ''scientific'' products often fail","Fear of being fooled again despite professional skepticism"]', '["''I''ve tried every evidence-based gut supplement and nothing works - maybe I''m unfixable''","''I thought my medical background would help me choose better, but I keep failing''","''Even the products with clinical studies don''t work for me - what''s wrong with my body?''"]', '2025-12-01 13:15:27.362897+00'), ('06cf8d8b-7818-4753-a966-78233924c39b', '17d26309-520b-45ec-b5d5-92512e2f6620', 'a73172c2-227e-42b6-8782-176c65c68499', '6', 'Scientific Credibility Crisis', 'Deep frustration and intellectual embarrassment about not being able to solve their gut health puzzle despite extensive research and scientific literacy. They pride themselves on evidence-based decisions but feel stupid for not cracking this particular code.', '["Intellectual pride damaged by inability to solve a ''simple'' health problem","Embarrassment about gaps in their supposedly comprehensive health knowledge","Frustration with conflicting research and lack of athletic-specific studies","Self-doubt about research and evaluation skills after repeated failures","Pressure to maintain reputation as the ''health expert'' in their circle"]', '["''I can analyze VO2 max studies but can''t figure out my own digestive system''","''People ask me for nutrition advice, but I can''t even fix my own gut health''","''I''ve read hundreds of papers on gut health but still feel clueless about what actually works''"]', '2025-12-01 13:17:27.218704+00'), ('07a1cd60-0bf4-4a66-8fec-93d5df7b5830', '17d26309-520b-45ec-b5d5-92512e2f6620', '260ec846-ba0f-43d5-82d9-4b2f93a4a440', '3', 'Premium Investment Validation Anxiety', 'Intense psychological pressure to justify spending significant money on health solutions by ensuring they reflect genuine scientific superiority, not just marketing. Their medical knowledge of actual production costs and pharmaceutical pricing creates skepticism about premium supplements while their desperation drives willingness to pay.', '["Loss aversion from previous expensive supplement failures","Professional knowledge of manufacturing costs creating price skepticism","Need to validate high spending through measurable superior outcomes","Fear of being financially manipulated by health marketing"]', '["''I''m spending more on supplements than some people spend on groceries - this better be revolutionary''","''I know this probably costs $5 to make but I''m paying $200 - I need proof it''s worth it''","''My medical training tells me this pricing is inflated but I''m desperate enough to try anyway''"]', '2025-12-01 13:15:27.362897+00'), ('0e235851-58d1-4a60-95ad-afb01510c3f3', '17d26309-520b-45ec-b5d5-92512e2f6620', '22dd4de4-07b3-493e-8448-13c1f69921de', '6', 'Social Health Parenting Judgment Fear', 'Constant anxiety about being judged by other parents, family members, or healthcare providers for their health choices, especially when pursuing premium or unconventional solutions. They fear being seen as extreme, neglectful, or falling for marketing hype.', '["Social comparison pressure with other parents'' seemingly effortless health approaches","Fear of medical professionals dismissing or criticizing their supplement choices","Anxiety about extended family questioning their parenting health decisions","Imposter syndrome about being ''extra'' or obsessive about health","Defensive positioning about spending premium amounts on family nutrition"]', '["''The other soccer moms think I''m crazy for researching ingredients this much''","''My mother-in-law rolls her eyes when she sees our supplement routine''","''I hide how much we spend on health products because people wouldn''t understand''"]', '2025-12-01 13:16:23.898139+00'), ('0f003404-ceb2-4913-8caf-5f6c300b557d', '17d26309-520b-45ec-b5d5-92512e2f6620', 'a73172c2-227e-42b6-8782-176c65c68499', '4', 'Competitive Paranoia About Secret Advantages', 'Consuming anxiety that competitors have discovered superior gut health protocols that provide hidden performance advantages while they struggle with the same old digestive issues. This creates obsessive research behavior and fear of missing the ''one thing'' that could transform their performance.', '["Hypercompetitive nature that can''t accept any disadvantage","Fear that successful competitors have nutritional secrets they don''t","Obsessive need to optimize every possible performance variable","Paranoia about falling behind in the ''optimization arms race''","Envy watching others recover faster or perform more consistently"]', '["''I wonder if the athletes who never seem to have gut issues know something I don''t''","''When someone PRs consistently, I obsess over what they''re doing differently''","''I stay up late researching protocols because I''m terrified of missing the breakthrough''"]', '2025-12-01 13:17:27.218704+00'), ('0fb10a88-02db-4e11-8945-d8ac091f0e04', '17d26309-520b-45ec-b5d5-92512e2f6620', '22dd4de4-07b3-493e-8448-13c1f69921de', '8', 'Information Overwhelm Decision Paralysis', 'Drowning in conflicting health information and research while feeling pressure to make perfect decisions for their family''s wellbeing. The responsibility of choosing correctly for multiple family members creates analysis paralysis and constant second-guessing of their conclusions.', '["Perfectionist pressure to find the ''one right answer'' for family health","Cognitive overload from conflicting expert opinions and research studies","Fear of missing crucial information that could change their decision","Responsibility anxiety about consequences of choosing wrong with limited information","Time pressure to make decisions while wanting to research everything thoroughly"]', '["''Every expert says something different - how do I know who to trust with my kids'' health?''","''I''ve been researching for months but feel more confused than when I started''","''What if there''s some study I missed that shows this isn''t safe for children?''"]', '2025-12-01 13:16:23.898139+00'), ('13a30ae3-6045-47f9-8e0e-308bef7fa521', '17d26309-520b-45ec-b5d5-92512e2f6620', 'faf5c581-0a78-4291-a5d6-68df043f2146', '2', 'Data-Driven Decision Paralysis', 'Their systematic approach backfires when applied to health decisions, creating endless research loops without clear conclusions. The abundance of conflicting information and lack of personal baseline data creates anxiety about making any decision at all.', '["Need for certainty in uncertain biological systems","Fear of making suboptimal choices with incomplete data","Perfectionist paralysis when data points contradict","Anxiety about opportunity cost of wrong decisions","Frustration with subjective vs. objective health measures"]', '["''I''ve been researching probiotics for 3 months and I''m more confused than when I started''","''Every study seems to contradict the last one - how am I supposed to decide?''","''I need baseline microbiome data but the tests are expensive and unreliable''"]', '2025-12-01 13:15:08.295705+00'), ('159d3f36-7e27-4bc5-ad40-9a77d4b76160', '17d26309-520b-45ec-b5d5-92512e2f6620', 'f81beda1-abd9-4969-993c-05a62b4ff695', '1', 'Time-running-out desperation', 'Paralyzing fear that critical intervention windows for healthy aging are closing while they''re still researching and deliberating. Every day of delay feels like irreversible loss of vitality preservation opportunity. The urgency to act wars with their methodical research nature, creating constant anxiety about missed chances.', '["Mortality salience increasing with age milestones and peer health decline","Scientific understanding that aging interventions are most effective when started early","Perfectionist paralysis preventing timely action despite urgency awareness","Regret about past delays in health optimization creating pressure to act now","Fear that their careful research approach is actually sabotaging their health outcomes"]', '["''I''ve been researching gut health for six months while my digestion keeps getting worse - what if I''ve already waited too long?''","''Every birthday feels like another year I didn''t optimize my health properly''","''I watch my friends aging rapidly and wonder if I''m researching myself into the same decline''"]', '2025-12-01 13:17:49.094091+00'), ('176add19-d702-41d6-b265-12e1cc28e468', '17d26309-520b-45ec-b5d5-92512e2f6620', 'b0367578-4c47-4149-87f5-492db909fcf8', '9', 'Body Wisdom Disconnection', 'Painful disconnection from their body''s natural signals and wisdom after years of trying external solutions instead of developing internal awareness. They feel like strangers in their own body, unable to distinguish between normal sensations and warning signs, creating anxiety about their ability to self-regulate and make appropriate health decisions. This disconnection makes them doubt their capacity for natural healing and intuitive wellness.', '["Loss of confidence in natural body wisdom and self-regulation","Over-reliance on external health inputs rather than internal awareness","Anxiety about inability to interpret body signals correctly","Fear that they''ve damaged their natural healing capacity through supplement dependency","Disconnection from ancestral health wisdom and natural living"]', '["''I don''t even know what normal digestion feels like anymore after trying so many interventions''","''I''ve become so dependent on supplements that I don''t trust my body to function naturally''","''I feel disconnected from my body''s natural rhythms and signals''"]', '2025-12-01 13:18:08.278685+00'), ('1e6d93bd-bbe5-44e6-b527-f3cbaf60dcb6', '17d26309-520b-45ec-b5d5-92512e2f6620', '9d33d01f-5215-4051-b58f-76f33fc2e6df', '4', 'Analysis Paralysis from Information Overload', 'Mental exhaustion from endless research cycles that lead to contradictory information and decision paralysis. Their analytical nature becomes a curse as they get lost in research rabbit holes without making progress on their actual health issues.', '["Perfectionism preventing them from making decisions with incomplete information","Fear that insufficient research will lead to another expensive mistake","Overwhelm from conflicting studies and expert opinions","Procrastination masked as thorough research to avoid potential failure"]', '["''I have 47 browser tabs open researching gut health and I''m more confused than ever''","''Every study seems to contradict the last one - I don''t know what to believe''","''I''ve been researching for three months but haven''t tried anything new''"]', '2025-12-01 13:16:05.658524+00'), ('1edfdece-732e-4da0-94bd-be54e1cf59e4', '17d26309-520b-45ec-b5d5-92512e2f6620', '9d33d01f-5215-4051-b58f-76f33fc2e6df', '6', 'Placebo Effect Self-Doubt and Reality Distortion', 'Profound confusion about their ability to accurately assess their own body''s responses after multiple supplement failures. They question whether any perceived improvements were real or imagined, creating deep uncertainty about their physical self-awareness.', '["Loss of confidence in their ability to read their own body''s signals","Fear that hope and expectation bias clouded their judgment","Uncertainty about what constitutes genuine improvement vs. wishful thinking","Anxiety that they can''t trust their own experience and perceptions"]', '["''I thought that probiotic was helping but maybe I just wanted it to work''","''I don''t know if I actually feel better or if I''m just convincing myself''","''How can I tell if something is really working when I''ve been wrong so many times?''"]', '2025-12-01 13:16:05.658524+00'), ('1fdd7427-c600-43a3-9bec-6cc1f4b597c8', '17d26309-520b-45ec-b5d5-92512e2f6620', '9d33d01f-5215-4051-b58f-76f33fc2e6df', '1', 'Intellectual Identity Crisis from Repeated Failures', 'Deep psychological wound from being deceived by supplement companies despite their careful research and high intelligence. They pride themselves on being analytical and evidence-based, yet have repeatedly made expensive mistakes that make them question their judgment abilities.', '["Cognitive dissonance between self-perception as smart decision-maker and repeated poor choices","Imposter syndrome about their health expertise after multiple supplement failures","Fear of intellectual humiliation from being fooled again despite sophisticated vetting","Identity threat to their role as the ''health-savvy'' person in their social circle"]', '["''I have a PhD and spent weeks researching, how did I still pick wrong?''","''People used to ask me for health advice, now I don''t trust my own judgment''","''I feel like an idiot for falling for their marketing despite reading all the studies''"]', '2025-12-01 13:16:05.658524+00'), ('22b44889-07d0-434b-a6c0-6e1089d54221', '17d26309-520b-45ec-b5d5-92512e2f6620', 'faf5c581-0a78-4291-a5d6-68df043f2146', '9', 'Professional Image Protection Desperation', 'Intense fear that visible health issues will damage their reputation as someone who ''has it all figured out.'' They desperately hide digestive problems, fatigue, and other symptoms that contradict their optimized professional persona.', '["Professional reputation anxiety tied to health image","Fear of appearing weak or uncontrolled to colleagues","Imposter syndrome about being ''wellness expert'' among peers","Social desirability pressure in achievement-oriented culture","Terror of professional consequences from health vulnerabilities"]', '["''I can''t let my team see me crash in afternoon meetings''","''People come to me for health advice - they can''t know I''m struggling with gut issues''","''My professional brand depends on being the optimized, high-energy person''"]', '2025-12-01 13:15:08.295705+00'), ('232302f1-4852-42d3-9c2c-e6e99c135ef9', '17d26309-520b-45ec-b5d5-92512e2f6620', 'a73172c2-227e-42b6-8782-176c65c68499', '8', 'Clean Label Compromise Torture', 'Agonizing internal conflict between their values-driven need for clean, natural supplements and their desperate desire for something that actually works. They torture themselves over every artificial ingredient while feeling like hypocrites for potentially compromising their health principles.', '["Identity conflict between health values and performance desperation","Fear of long-term health consequences from artificial supplement ingredients","Guilt about potentially betraying their clean-living athletic identity","Anxiety about what artificial ingredients might do to their carefully maintained system","Self-judgment for considering ''impure'' solutions due to desperation"]', '["''I''m so desperate for results I''m considering supplements with artificial additives - what''s wrong with me?''","''Every effective product seems to have some sketchy ingredient that goes against everything I believe''","''I preach clean eating but I''m tempted by synthetic solutions because nothing natural works''"]', '2025-12-01 13:17:27.218704+00'), ('26e31b48-167c-4ac8-8fd4-e5c0011496ed', '17d26309-520b-45ec-b5d5-92512e2f6620', 'b2cbef7c-c10d-4039-a5ec-49b6d3d69b74', '3', 'Hypervigilant Trigger Paralysis', 'Constant state of anxious hypervigilance about every food, supplement, or treatment potentially causing a symptom flare. This creates exhausting decision paralysis where they want to try healing interventions but are terrified of making their condition worse, leading to analysis paralysis and self-limiting behaviors.', '["Traumatic memories of severe symptom flares triggered by ''safe'' products","Fear that one wrong choice could cause weeks or months of suffering","Learned helplessness from unpredictable symptom patterns","Catastrophic thinking about worst-case scenarios from new interventions","Loss of trust in their own body''s signals and reactions"]', '["''I spent three hours researching a single ingredient because I''m terrified it might trigger a flare''","''I have a cart full of supplements I want to try but I''m too scared to order them''","''Last time I tried something new, I ended up in the ER - now I question everything''"]', '2025-12-01 13:15:46.785116+00'), ('27498967-a5d2-4144-be1d-34754a38ff5f', '17d26309-520b-45ec-b5d5-92512e2f6620', '678b303d-d8b7-4796-8a3d-2b97213da873', '5', 'Time Scarcity Optimization Pressure', 'Intense psychological pressure to find the one perfect, comprehensive solution that eliminates all health decision-making from their mental bandwidth. The gap between their need for health optimization and their complete lack of time creates a desperate search for the ''holy grail'' solution that can work without their ongoing attention.', '["Cognitive load reduction desperation in already overwhelmed mental space","Perfectionism driving search for one ultimate solution rather than multiple good ones","Time poverty anxiety about health maintenance competing with career demands","Efficiency maximization compulsion applied to biological processes","Decision fatigue avoidance in non-core expertise area"]', '["''I need health to be like my automated investment portfolio - set it and forget it''","''I don''t have bandwidth to manage a complex supplement routine on top of everything else''","''There has to be one thing that just works without me having to think about it constantly''"]', '2025-12-01 13:14:49.482851+00'), ('2aae8bd1-bf7b-4578-9028-0c1352f4234b', '17d26309-520b-45ec-b5d5-92512e2f6620', 'ba978ac4-68e6-484a-a12a-f72a43ab0f82', '8', 'Health optimization plateau frustration', 'Despite investing thousands in functional medicine consultations, advanced testing, and premium interventions, they''ve hit a plateau where additional improvements feel impossible to achieve. This creates deep frustration and self-doubt about whether they''re missing some crucial piece of the health optimization puzzle they should understand.', '["Perfectionist need to continuously optimize and improve health metrics","Fear that they''ve reached the limits of natural intervention effectiveness","Anxiety that other health-conscious peers are achieving better results","Self-doubt about their ability to interpret and apply complex health information"]', '["''I''ve optimized everything I can think of but I still don''t feel as vibrant as I should''","''Other people in my functional medicine community seem to get better results - what am I doing wrong?''","''I''ve invested so much in my health but I feel like I''ve hit a wall in my progress''"]', '2025-12-01 13:17:04.821693+00'), ('31b53843-b4ff-4249-8660-0a16c03daf62', '17d26309-520b-45ec-b5d5-92512e2f6620', '678b303d-d8b7-4796-8a3d-2b97213da873', '1', 'Executive Performance Deterioration Terror', 'Deep existential fear that their declining energy and cognitive sharpness will expose them as no longer capable of peak leadership, threatening their core professional identity. This isn''t just about feeling tired - it''s about the terror of being ''found out'' as past their prime in high-stakes situations where mental acuity directly impacts their authority and career trajectory.', '["Impostor syndrome amplification during energy crashes","Professional identity threat when cognitive function wavers","Competitive displacement anxiety from younger, more energetic peers","Authority erosion fear when struggling to maintain executive presence","Career mortality salience - recognizing finite high-performance window"]', '["''I blanked during the board presentation and could see them questioning my capability''","''My 35-year-old VP seems sharper than me lately - that''s terrifying''","''What if they realize I''m not the powerhouse they hired anymore?''"]', '2025-12-01 13:14:49.482851+00'), ('36c99fb6-1d2a-491f-a818-6a2f1b1a23f2', '17d26309-520b-45ec-b5d5-92512e2f6620', 'b2cbef7c-c10d-4039-a5ec-49b6d3d69b74', '4', 'Invisible Suffering Isolation', 'Profound loneliness from having a condition that''s invisible to others, leading to constant need to justify their limitations while appearing ''normal'' on the outside. They feel misunderstood, judged, and isolated from healthy people who can''t comprehend their daily struggles, creating deep social disconnection.', '["Having to constantly explain and justify their limitations to others","Feeling judged as lazy or dramatic when they can''t participate fully","Lack of understanding from family and friends about invisible symptoms","Social media comparisons with seemingly healthy, active peers","Feeling excluded from normal social activities due to dietary restrictions"]', '["''People see me looking fine and don''t understand why I can''t just eat pizza at the office party''","''My family thinks I''m being dramatic about my food restrictions until they see me during a flare''","''I feel like I''m living in a different world than everyone else - they just don''t get it''"]', '2025-12-01 13:15:46.785116+00'), ('3a3ddd35-5b93-4662-b5f0-b68cab7ff4dc', '17d26309-520b-45ec-b5d5-92512e2f6620', 'ba978ac4-68e6-484a-a12a-f72a43ab0f82', '7', 'Practitioner-grade authenticity verification paralysis', 'Their functional medicine education has shown them the vast quality gap between practitioner-dispensed and consumer supplements, creating paralyzing uncertainty about whether any direct-to-consumer product can meet therapeutic standards. They''re trapped between needing practitioner-grade interventions and wanting independence in their health choices.', '["Knowledge of supplement industry quality control failures","Need for independence from constant practitioner oversight","Fear of compromising their health protocol with inferior products","Anxiety about making uninformed choices despite extensive education"]', '["''How do I know this meets the same standards as what my functional medicine doctor would recommend?''","''I want to be proactive between appointments but I''m terrified of choosing something that undermines my protocol''","''Is this actually pharmaceutical-grade or just marketing to people like me who know to ask?''"]', '2025-12-01 13:17:04.821693+00'), ('3b81c03f-e1fb-43db-87dc-c5dc58f6b600', '17d26309-520b-45ec-b5d5-92512e2f6620', 'faf5c581-0a78-4291-a5d6-68df043f2146', '7', 'Time Efficiency Guilt Complex', 'Constant internal conflict between wanting comprehensive health optimization and needing time-efficient solutions. They feel guilty about shortcuts but anxious about time investment, creating decision paralysis.', '["Perfectionist guilt about taking health shortcuts","Time scarcity anxiety from demanding work schedules","Fear that efficient solutions aren''t thorough enough","Identity conflict between optimization and efficiency","Worry about compromising health for convenience"]', '["''I know I should meal prep and take 15 supplements, but I barely have time for breakfast''","''Am I being lazy by wanting a simple solution, or smart about time management?''","''Every morning I stress about whether I''m doing enough for my health''"]', '2025-12-01 13:15:08.295705+00'), ('3c961e3b-7ef5-4c3e-a815-3e48f88c1eba', '17d26309-520b-45ec-b5d5-92512e2f6620', 'fdfbe62f-ccdf-492e-842e-d07fb82e063c', '8', 'Community Status Competence Anxiety', 'Fear of losing credibility and respect within their biohacking community when they can''t demonstrate the impressive results that others report. This threatens their identity as a successful optimizer and creates pressure to either lie about results or find breakthrough solutions.', '["Social comparison pressure in optimization-focused communities","Fear of being exposed as unsuccessful despite significant investment","Imposter syndrome in high-achieving peer groups","Status anxiety about falling behind network standards","Identity threat when results don''t match community expectations"]', '["''Everyone in my forum shares amazing progress photos while I look the same''","''I avoid biohacker meetups because I have nothing impressive to report''","''I feel like a fraud when people ask about my latest breakthroughs''"]', '2025-12-01 13:16:43.715484+00'), ('427355b6-6000-48c2-a276-0f3198c94e64', '17d26309-520b-45ec-b5d5-92512e2f6620', 'fdfbe62f-ccdf-492e-842e-d07fb82e063c', '7', 'Cellular Aging Existential Dread', 'Deep fear that despite all their optimization efforts, cellular damage and aging are progressing faster than their interventions can repair. This creates urgent pressure to find more powerful solutions before irreversible decline occurs.', '["Mortality salience despite optimization efforts","Fear that current interventions are insufficient against aging","Anxiety about time window closing for cellular repair","Panic about missing critical intervention period","Existential terror about biological inevitability despite control efforts"]', '["''I feel like I''m losing the race against cellular damage despite everything I do''","''My recovery times are getting longer and I''m terrified optimization isn''t enough''","''What if I''ve already missed the window for preventing age-related decline?''"]', '2025-12-01 13:16:43.715484+00'), ('48e183e4-325c-40e1-a9f7-32e3f73172d3', '17d26309-520b-45ec-b5d5-92512e2f6620', 'b0367578-4c47-4149-87f5-492db909fcf8', '2', 'Invisible Decline Panic', 'Haunting fear that their digestive issues, brain fog, and energy crashes are early warning signs of serious health decline that others can''t see yet but will eventually become obvious. They worry they''re on a trajectory toward chronic illness, autoimmune disease, or premature aging while appearing healthy on the surface. This creates urgent anxiety about preventing invisible damage before it becomes irreversible.', '["Catastrophic thinking about minor health symptoms escalating","Fear of losing control over their health trajectory and future quality of life","Anxiety about genetic predispositions manifesting through poor gut health","Terror of becoming a cautionary tale among health-conscious peers","Temporal anxiety about limited time window for effective prevention"]', '["''What if this bloating is actually the start of something serious that doctors aren''t catching?''","''I look fine now but I can feel my body breaking down from the inside''","''My grandmother''s autoimmune issues started with digestive problems just like mine''"]', '2025-12-01 13:18:08.278685+00'), ('49638847-5368-43f5-bc86-a16e9435c154', '17d26309-520b-45ec-b5d5-92512e2f6620', 'ba978ac4-68e6-484a-a12a-f72a43ab0f82', '2', 'Cellular degeneration terror', 'An underlying horror that despite all their knowledge and investments, cellular damage is accumulating faster than their interventions can repair it. They obsess over whether their current approach is truly preventing the mitochondrial dysfunction and oxidative stress they understand leads to aging and disease.', '["Knowledge of how cellular damage compounds over time creates urgency","Fear that their current energy decline signals irreversible aging","Terror of becoming dependent on medications they''re trying to avoid","Anxiety that their preventive approach isn''t aggressive enough"]', '["''What if my cells are dying faster than I can repair them with these basic supplements?''","''I understand the science - every day I wait, more mitochondrial damage accumulates''","''I''m terrified I''ll end up like my parents despite everything I know about prevention''"]', '2025-12-01 13:17:04.821693+00'), ('4bcf882d-b67d-4b33-8527-7078590e26a2', '17d26309-520b-45ec-b5d5-92512e2f6620', 'a73172c2-227e-42b6-8782-176c65c68499', '5', 'Training Investment Betrayal', 'Bitter frustration that their massive investment in training time, coaching, and discipline is being sabotaged by digestive issues they can''t control. They feel betrayed by their own body when gut problems prevent them from executing the training they''ve planned and paid for.', '["Resentment that digestive issues are stealing returns on training investment","Guilt about wasted coaching sessions due to gut-related performance drops","Anger at their body for not supporting their dedication and sacrifice","Fear that gut issues make their training investment pointless","Frustration with lack of control over digestive system despite controlling 